
# |<------ Preferably using up to 50 chars ------>|<------------------->|
# <tag><group>: <subject> (Max 72 char)
# --------------------
# Examples:
#   feat(core): Implement automated commit messages
#   fix: Solve the last bug issue
# --------------------
# Tag can be:
#   feat      (new feature)
#   fix       (bug fix)
#   refactor  (refactoring code)
#   style     (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   doc       (changes to documentation)
#   test      (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   version   (version bump / new release; no production code change)
#   script    (changes in scripts; no production code change)
#   community (edits community rules; no production code change)
#   hack      (temporary fix to make things move forward; avoid it)
#   wip       (work in progress; for intermediate commits)
#
# (Optional) Group is:
#   (module name) The name of any repository internal folder that 
#   represents a module, write the name between parentheses
#   Examples: (core), (regex), or others
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#   Capitalize the subject line
#   Use the imperative mood in the subject line
#   Do not end the subject line with a period
